## 1. Mission & Product Identity

### 1.1 What is HydraScan?

HydraScan is a **practitioner-first recovery intelligence platform** for the Hydrawav3 ecosystem. It captures client movement and recovery signals using QuickPose on-device pose estimation, converts them into a live Recovery Graph, recommends a personalized Hydrawav3 session, launches that session on a real HydraWav3Pro device through the MQTT Control API, and tracks outcomes across visits so recovery becomes continuous instead of isolated.

### 1.2 What HydraScan is NOT

- NOT a generic body-scanning app
- NOT a medical diagnosis engine
- NOT a practitioner replacement layer
- NOT a consumer wellness app that happens to have a device connection
- It IS a Hydrawav3-native intelligence, orchestration, and continuity platform

### 1.3 Core Promise (one line)

> Turn each 9-minute Hydrawav3 session into a persistent recovery intelligence loop.

### 1.4 Pitch Sentence

> HydraScan turns a 9-minute Hydrawav3 session into a persistent, practitioner-guided recovery intelligence system that runs on real Hydrawav3Pro hardware.

### 1.5 The Hydrawav3 Flywheel: Know вҶ’ Act вҶ’ Learn

Everything HydraScan does maps to this flywheel:

| Stage | What happens | HydraScan responsibility |
|-------|-------------|-------------------------|
| **Know** | Client signs in, completes rapid intake, highlights body zones, performs guided QuickPose movement captures | QuickPose computes landmarks, joint angles, ROM, asymmetry. HydraScan merges with recovery signals, wearables, profile history вҶ’ outputs a 60-second Recovery Map and Recovery Graph |
| **Act** | Practitioner opens client profile, reviews Recovery Map, approves/edits recommended session | HydraScan recommends Sun/Moon placement, modality mix, intensity, sequence, duration вҶ’ emits typed `SessionConfig` вҶ’ publishes to target device via MQTT Control API |
| **Learn** | Client and practitioner complete post-session feedback and follow-up check-ins | HydraScan records subjective change, re-test values, adherence, next-visit signals вҶ’ updates Recovery Graph against exact payload that ran вҶ’ improves future recommendations |

### 1.6 Target Users

| User | Context | Primary need |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **Physical Therapists** | Post-surgical recovery, chronic pain management support, neurological rehab, sports injury recovery | Objective intake, faster protocol selection, outcome visibility |
| **Chiropractors** | Pre-adjustment tissue prep, post-adjustment recovery, soft-tissue work between visits | Quick session personalization, throughput, adherence |
| **Sports Trainers** | Pre-game warm-up, post-game recovery, athletic performance support | Fast turnaround, return-to-training readiness |
| **Medical Spas & Wellness Centers** | Pain relief add-on, medspa service, destination spa upgrade | Hands-off premium service that scales, ROI visibility |

