#### Limitations (from Hydrawav3)
- **Lighting matters** вҖ” rPPG works best in stable, good lighting. Outdoor + exercise = harder.
- **Motion artifacts** вҖ” Active exercise makes heart rate extraction noisier.
- **Accuracy ceiling** вҖ” Video-based HR is Вұ5вҖ“10 bpm vs. clinical Вұ1вҖ“2 bpm. This is screening, not diagnosis.
- **Privacy** вҖ” Face video requires consent. Get it before filming.
- **Multi-camera > single camera** вҖ” OpenCap with 2+ phones significantly outperforms single-angle.

