## 3. Constraints & Guardrails

### 3.1 Language & Compliance Rules (MANDATORY)

Every UI string, API response, report output, and LLM-generated text MUST comply with these rules. Violations will hurt judging scores.

| ALWAYS USE | NEVER USE |
|-----------|-----------|
| recovery, wellness, mobility, performance | medical device, clinical, diagnostic |
| supports, empowers, enhances | treats, cures, diagnoses, heals |
| practitioner-first, hands-off | replaces the practitioner |
| supports inflammation management | reduces inflammation |
| the body heals itself | we heal the body |
| movement insights, recovery signals | clinical findings, medical results |
| wellness indicators | diagnostic indicators |

### 3.2 Brand Language
- **Hydrawav3** is always spelled with a lowercase `w`
- The company name is **Hydrawav3** (not HydraWav, Hydra Wav, etc.)
- In API/code contexts, the official topic string is `"HydraWav3Pro/config"` вҖ” use this exact casing

### 3.3 Clinic Compatibility Requirements
- Any in-clinic interaction must fit inside a realistic workflow
- Assume 60вҖ“80 patients per day
- Practitioner touch time stays under **two minutes** per decision point
- Intake for the client should complete in **under 60 seconds**

### 3.4 Personalization Requirements
- Every patient is different
- Rules-based one-size-fits-all logic scores LOWER than systems that adapt
- The system must show WHY a recommendation was made, not just WHAT it is

### 3.5 Technical Constraints
- iOS app must use SwiftUI
- QuickPose is the pose estimation SDK (not raw MediaPipe)
- The MQTT API payload must ALWAYS be stringified JSON, not raw objects
- The MQTT topic is ALWAYS `"HydraWav3Pro/config"`
- Device targeting is ALWAYS by MAC address
- JWT tokens from `/api/v1/auth/login` are used for all API calls

### 3.6 Privacy & Consent
- Face video requires explicit consent before filming
- Patient data must be scoped to clinic workspaces (no cross-clinic leakage)
- Session logs should not contain personally identifiable information outside the authenticated context
- rPPG face data should be processed on-device and not stored as raw video

