### 6.3 Recovery Score & Continuity

The Recovery Score is a single number (0вҖ“100) that tracks the client's recovery trajectory between visits. It is computed from:

- Recent session outcomes (stiffness deltas, mobility improvements)
- Daily check-in data (if any)
- Wearable data (HRV trends, sleep quality)
- Session frequency and adherence

```typescript
// backend/supabase/functions/recovery-score/index.ts

function computeRecoveryScore(
  recentOutcomes: Outcome[],
  recentCheckins: DailyCheckin[],
  wearableContext: WearableContext | null,
  sessionFrequency: number,  // sessions per week
): number {
  let score = 50; // Baseline

  // Factor 1: Outcome trend (up to Вұ20 points)
  if (recentOutcomes.length > 0) {
    const avgDelta = recentOutcomes.reduce((sum, o) =>
      sum + ((o.stiffness_before - o.stiffness_after) / 10), 0) / recentOutcomes.length;
    score += avgDelta * 20;
  }

  // Factor 2: Check-in trend (up to Вұ10 points)
  if (recentCheckins.length > 0) {
    const avgFeeling = recentCheckins.reduce((sum, c) =>
      sum + c.overall_feeling, 0) / recentCheckins.length;
    score += (avgFeeling - 3) * 5;  // 3 is neutral
  }

  // Factor 3: Wearable (up to Вұ10 points)
  if (wearableContext) {
    if (wearableContext.hrv > 50) score += 5;
    if (wearableContext.sleepScore > 75) score += 5;
  }

  // Factor 4: Adherence (up to +10 points)
  if (sessionFrequency >= 2) score += 10;
  else if (sessionFrequency >= 1) score += 5;

  return Math.max(0, Math.min(100, Math.round(score)));
}
```

