## Final Notes for Coding Agents

### Agent coordination model

- Each phase can be developed in parallel after Phase 0 completes.
- Phase 1 (auth) and Phase 2 (MQTT) can run in parallel.
- Phase 3 (QuickPose) can start after Phase 0 (SDK installed).
- Phase 4 (recommendation engine) needs Phase 3 outputs but can be stubbed.
- Phase 5 (practitioner dashboard) depends on Phase 2 + Phase 4.
- Phase 6 (client app) depends on Phase 1 + Phase 3.
- Phase 7 (outcomes) depends on Phase 5 + Phase 6.
- Phase 8 (analytics) depends on Phase 7.
- Phase 9 (integration) depends on all prior phases.

